@startuml
title UC reconcile-role
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor<<Command>> LightBlue
  BackgroundColor<<Aggregate>> Khaki
  BackgroundColor<<Event>> Orange
}

actor "Ansible Operator" as operator

package "reconcile-role" {
  rectangle "EXASOL_ROLE\n(Aggregate)" as AGG <<Aggregate>>

  rectangle "CreateRole\n(Command)" as CMD_Create <<Command>>
  rectangle "RoleCreated\n(Event)" as EVT_Created <<Event>>

  rectangle "DropRole\n(Command, cascade)" as CMD_Drop <<Command>>
  rectangle "RoleDropped\n(Event)" as EVT_Dropped <<Event>>

  rectangle "PredictRoleChange\n(Command, check mode)\ncovers every branch above" as CMD_Predict <<Command>>
  rectangle "RoleChangePredicted\n(Event)\nsame plan, no statement executed" as EVT_Predicted <<Event>>
}

operator --> CMD_Create
operator --> CMD_Drop
operator --> CMD_Predict

CMD_Create --> AGG
AGG --> EVT_Created

CMD_Drop --> AGG
AGG --> EVT_Dropped

CMD_Predict --> AGG
AGG --> EVT_Predicted

note bottom of AGG
  When the role already exists (for CreateRole) or is already
  absent (for DropRole), the runtime issues no command and
  reports changed=false.

  Source scenario: specs/ansible_modules/exasol_role.feature
end note
@enduml
